{"url": "https://www.brit.co/this-is-the-10-sunscreen-lauren-conrad-cant-live-without/", "text": "Whether you\u2019re celebrating outdoors with a Fourth of July BBQ (like Eva Longoria) or heading out to see some epic fireworks, you\u2019ll want to make sure your skin is protected from the sun\u2019s harmful UVs with plenty of sunblock.\n\nBut not all SPF is created equal \u2014 in fact, there are three different types \u2014 and choosing the best one from drugstore shelves can be a daunting task. Unless you just so happen to be Lauren Conrad, that is. The 31-year-old mommy-to-be has a new go-to that she\u2019s wild about, and it\u2019s actually (gasp!) under $10.\n\nWhen it comes time to hit the beach, LC says it\u2019s Alba Botanica Hawaiian Sunscreen With SPF 45 ($9) that she\u2019s lathering up with. \u201cThere\u2019s a huge pump of it in my bathroom,\u201d she told Well & Good.\n\nIt\u2019s a wise choice for the pregnant reality alum, as not only is its green tea and aloe inclusive formula 100 percent vegetarian, but it\u2019s lightweight, stays water-resistant for up to 80 minutes, and reportedly dries in a flash. Those that care about the environment (read: all of us) will also be pleased to know that it\u2019s biodegradable and free of animal testing.\n\nIn short? It\u2019s the perfect product for those carefree beach days (like today), when you\u2019re hanging poolside in a bandeau (Conrad\u2019s fave, since it won\u2019t give you tan lines) and a caftan, LC-style. \u201cThere\u2019s just something glamorous about a lightweight caftan,\u201d she told the outlet.\n\nLooking good, mamma!\n\nWhat\u2019s your sunblock go-to? Share with us @BritandCo.\n\n(h/t E!; photos via Dimitrios Kambouris/Getty)", "images": ["data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 1245 700'%3E%3C/svg%3E", "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "https://www.facebook.com/tr?id=377612259624022&ev=PageView&noscript=1", "https://www.brit.co/media-library/brit-co-logo.pn